2
00:00:02,130 --> 00:00:04,620
learn the English phrase, I've had it!

3
00:00:04,620 --> 00:00:07,020
Now simply used, this simply means

4
00:00:07,020 --> 00:00:08,710
that you have had something.

5
00:00:08,710 --> 00:00:10,410
If someone says, have you had pizza?

6
00:00:10,410 --> 00:00:12,560
You could say I've had it and I liked it.

7
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:15,910
But we also use this phrase
to describe a situation,

8
00:00:15,910 --> 00:00:18,100
when you want something to stop.

9
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:20,070
It's been raining a lot here lately,

10
00:00:20,070 --> 00:00:22,120
you can maybe see some
puddles on the ground there

11
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:23,260
and I've had it.

12
00:00:23,260 --> 00:00:26,090
I've had it with all the
rain we've been having.

13
00:00:26,090 --> 00:00:28,450
That means that I wish it would stop.

14
00:00:28,450 --> 00:00:30,950
Sometimes I use this phrase
in the classroom too.

15
00:00:30,950 --> 00:00:33,580
When students are talking
too much, I can say, hey,

16
00:00:33,580 --> 00:00:36,790
I've had it with all of the talking there

17
00:00:36,790 --> 00:00:38,700
in the back of the room, please stop.

18
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,710
So, in English when you say I've had it,

19
00:00:40,710 --> 00:00:42,880
it means you want something to stop.

20
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:45,570
I've certainly had it with all this rain.

21
00:00:45,570 --> 00:00:48,170
It's just way too wet out
here, it's gotta stop soon

22
00:00:48,170 --> 00:00:52,500
