very nice rest of the fall.

23
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:55,360
The second phrase I wanted to
teach you today is the phrase

24
00:00:55,360 --> 00:00:57,070
to have it out with someone.

25
00:00:57,070 --> 00:00:58,320
When you have it out with someone,

26
00:00:58,320 --> 00:01:01,240
it means that you're annoyed
with someone about something

27
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:03,170
and maybe they're annoyed
with you about something,

28
00:01:03,170 --> 00:01:04,959
and eventually you argue about it

29
00:01:04,959 --> 00:01:08,060
or you discuss it strongly
would be a good word.

30
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:09,880
When you have it out with someone,

31
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:12,480
it usually means that there's
a little bit of arguing,

32
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:14,900
maybe some yelling involved as well.

33
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:19,400
Maybe my sister is doing
something regularly that annoys me

34
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,870
